// Setting up flask and the environment

1 - Install virtual environment (pip install virtualenv)
2 - Create a virtual environment in the API folder CMD: virtualenv env
3 - Activate the virtual environment. Navigate to "cd env/Scripts" and type "activate"
4- Go back to the original environment, and install Flask with "pip install flask"
5- Check if it is properly setup. Go to python: from flask import Flask

// Create the directory section of Flask
1 - Create the static directory CMD: mkdir static
2 - Create the templates directory CMD: mkdir templates
3 - Create the images directory CMD: mkdir images
